rComments: Not sure if it's because it was her first year teaching at the U of W or because she felt nervous with online courses but this class was horrible. No live lectures, which meant teaching yourself EVERYTHING and the provided pre-recorded lectures were extremely hard to follow. Had to drop the course because the grade was affecting my GPA so poorly

The professor is really great! She cares about her students a lot and really makes sure that the students understand the course material. Very passionate about her work and it creates a great chemistry in class. One of the best

Let's just say that I'm praying to have her again in the future, she has to be the best and most underrated teacher at the University. I hope that the University is open to allowing more Stats classes for Criminology just because of her.

She is absolutely great, I've never had a teacher that has cared as much about her students than her, she really goes out of her way to make class a fun experience and goes out of her way to make you succeed. If you take statistics, she is a MUST! She has natural charisma for days and a great educator, you can't ask for more.

I was a little worried about taking a class with Sarah since she was new and no one knew much about her. I can confidently say she is one of the sweetest and most genuine professors in our faculty. She will go out of her way to help her students succeed and she takes her time with the material (much more than Cheryl). TAKE HER FOR STATS !!

She's a fantastic teacher,  she goes very in-depth with the material and tries to make statistics as clear and concrete as possible. Somehow, she made statistics become my favourite course this semester. She's a really nice woman and I pray to have her again next year. She's really cool and still remembers how it is to be a student so it's great.
